reviewText: I THOUGHT THIS WAS A STANDUP COMEDY. IT'S NOT VERY INTERESTING AT ALL. A WASTE OF MY MONEY.
Wasn't a good movie. Very low budget made movie
LOVE ME SOME KATT WILLIAMS PLEASE HURRY UP AND COME TO LOS ANGELES, CA.

It's just not very good - it needed a lot more punch and verve, And being a lot dirtier would help. The men are gorgeous, but that won't carry a film alone. Poor script, poor acting, poor film. Even my cat covered her eyes -  see below.
The one star speaks for itself. This movie sucks.

Preacher son Samuel (Antoine Cleveland) borrowed money from night club owner "The Bruce" (Katt Williams). In order to pay it back, Samuel performs on stage as a male dancer.

The film is too much like the recently released "Chocolate City." Katt Williams has a few good lines, but nothing to write about.

Guide: F-bomb. Implied sex. Stripper nudity.
